      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\community-launchpad-proto-backup-pre-fix\\docs\\00_OVERVIEW.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # FirstGens Community — Overview\n2: \n3: ## What this is\n4: \n5: **A clickable UX/UI prototype** for a community platform supporting\n6: first-generation university students. It exists so stakeholders, designers,\n7: and prospective users can click through realistic flows, react to the visual\n8: design, and validate the information architecture *before* a single line of\n9: production code is written.\n10: \n11: It is built with React + TypeScript + TanStack Start + Tailwind, and uses\n12: **in-memory mock data** (plain typed arrays in `src/mock-data/`) — no\n13: database, no auth, no API.\n14: \n15: ## What this is NOT\n16: \n17: - **Not the production system.** The real system will be built on the\n18:   [Frappe Framework](https://frappeframework.com), composing two existing\n19:   open-source apps and one new custom app:\n20:   - [`frappe/lms`](https://github.com/frappe/lms) — courses, lessons, quizzes\n21:   - [`frappe/gameplan`](https://github.com/frappe/gameplan) — teams, spaces,\n22:     discussions, comments, reactions\n23:   - `fg_companion` (new, to be written) — events, mentor matching, AI settings\n24: - **Not a real ML pipeline.** The \"Flagged for check-in\" sentiment badge and\n25:   the \"Similar conversations\" suggestions are deliberate keyword-based stubs.\n26:   See [`02_WHATS_MOCKED_VS_REAL.md`](./02_WHATS_MOCKED_VS_REAL.md).\n27: - **Not a clinical tool.** The sentiment flag is a gentle nudge for a human\n28:   Space Admin to check in. It is not a diagnosis and never claims to be.\n29: \n30: ## Why structure it this way\n31: \n32: Because the prototype is intentionally **schema-faithful** to Frappe. Every\n33: TypeScript type in `src/mock-data/types.ts` mirrors a real Frappe DocType\n34: field-for-field where reasonable. When the time comes to throw the React\n35: code at the real backend, the porting work is a translation exercise, not a\n36: redesign. See [`01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md`](./01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md)\n37: and [`03_PORTING_GUIDE.md`](./03_PORTING_GUIDE.md).\n38: \n39: ## Pages\n40: \n41: - **Home Feed** — discussions across all visible Spaces, newest first\n42: - **Space page** — one Space, with a \"New Post\" composer\n43: - **Post detail** — full post + threaded comments + mocked \"Similar posts\"\n44: - **Events** — card grid of events, RSVP writes to in-memory attendees\n45: - **Mentor Match** — request a mentor + see your current matches\n46: - **Courses** — thin stub; the real LMS lives in `frappe/lms`\n47: - **Member profile** — bio + recent posts\n\n(End of file - total 47 lines)\n</content>",
      "status": "success",
