    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "read",
      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\community-launchpad-proto-backup-pre-fix\\\\docs\\\\01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md\"}",
      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\community-launchpad-proto-backup-pre-fix\\docs\\01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Schema Mapping: TypeScript ↔ Frappe DocTypes\n2: \n3: > **Current storage layer.** In-memory mock data (`src/mock-data/`) because the\n4: > backend is disabled in this environment. The TypeScript shapes\n5: > (`GPTeam`, `GPProject`, `GPDiscussion`, `GPComment`, `GPReaction`,\n6: > `GPUserProfile`, `LMSCourse`, `FGEvent`, `FGEventAttendee`,\n7: > `FGMentorMatch`, `FGAISettings`) are deliberately shaped to match the real\n8: > Frappe DocTypes documented below. The same shapes will become Supabase\n9: > tables when Lovable Cloud is enabled — a contained, mechanical change in\n10: > `src/mock-data/store.ts` only — and those Supabase tables map 1:1 to the\n11: > Frappe DocTypes here. Component code never changes.\n12: \n13: All field names below were verified against the live `.json` files in\n14: [`frappe/gameplan`](https://github.com/frappe/gameplan/tree/main/gameplan/gameplan/doctype)\n15: and [`frappe/lms`](https://github.com/frappe/lms/tree/main/lms/lms/doctype) on\n16: their `main` branches.\n17: \n18: ## Frappe meta fields (always present, never declared)\n19: \n20: Every Frappe document carries these standard fields automatically:\n21: \n22: | Frappe meta field | Prototype alias |\n23: |---|---|\n24: | `name` | `id` |\n25: | `owner` | `author_id` (where surfaced) |\n26: | `creation` | `created_at` (where surfaced) |\n27: | `modified`, `modified_by`, `docstatus`, `idx` | not surfaced in prototype |\n28: \n29: Child-table rows additionally carry `parent`, `parenttype`, `parentfield`.\n30: \n31: ## frappe/gameplan\n32: \n33: ### `GPTeam` ↔ `GP Team`\n34: File: `gameplan/gameplan/doctype/gp_team/gp_team.json` · Autoname: Prompt\n35: \n36: | TS field | Frappe field | Type |\n37: |---|---|---|\n38: | `id` | `name` | (autoname Prompt) |\n39: | `title` | `title` | Data, reqd |\n40: | `icon` | `icon` | Data |\n41: | `is_private` | `is_private` | Check |\n42: | `archived_at` | `archived_at` | Datetime |\n43: | `archived_by` | `archived_by` | Link → User |\n44: \n45: Not surfaced: `members` (Table → GP Member), `cover_image`,\n46: `cover_image_position`, `readme`.\n47: \n48: ### `GPProject` ↔ `GP Project` (UI label \"Space\")\n49: File: `gameplan/gameplan/doctype/gp_project/gp_project.json` · Autoname: autoincrement\n50: \n51: | TS field | Frappe field | Type |\n52: |---|---|---|\n53: | `id` | `name` | autoincrement |\n54: | `title` | `title` | Data, reqd |\n55: | `description` | `description` | Text Editor |\n56: | `status` | `status` | Select: Open / Completed |\n57: | `team` | `team` | Link → GP Team |\n58: | `progress` | `progress` | Percent |\n59: | `icon` | `icon` | Data |\n60: | `readme` | `readme` | Text Editor |\n61: | `tasks_count` | `tasks_count` | Int, read_only |\n62: | `discussions_count` | `discussions_count` | Int, read_only |\n63: | `archived_at` | `archived_at` | Datetime |\n64: | `archived_by` | `archived_by` | Link → User |\n65: | `is_private` | `is_private` | Check |\n66: \n67: Not surfaced: `members` (Table → GP Member), `is_followed` (is_virtual=1, computed).\n68: \n69: ### `GPDiscussion` ↔ `GP Discussion` (UI label \"Post\")\n70: File: `gameplan/gameplan/doctype/gp_discussion/gp_discussion.json` · Autoname: autoincrement\n71: \n72: | TS field | Frappe field | Type |\n73: |---|---|---|\n74: | `id` | `name` | autoincrement |\n75: | `project` | `project` | Link → GP Project, reqd |\n76: | `team` | `team` | Link → GP Team, fetch_from: project.team |\n77: | `status` | `status` | Data |\n78: | `title` | `title` | Data, reqd |\n79: | `slug` | `slug` | Data |\n80: | `content` | `content` | Text Editor (HTML) |\n81: | `last_post_at` | `last_post_at` | Datetime |\n82: | `last_post_by` | `last_post_by` | Link → User |\n83: | `comments_count` | `comments_count` | Int, read_only |\n84: | `participants_count` | `participants_count` | Int, read_only |\n85: | `closed_at` | `closed_at` | Datetime |\n86: | `closed_by` | `closed_by` | Link → User |\n87: | `pinned_at` | `pinned_at` | Datetime |\n88: | `pinned_by` | `pinned_by` | Link → User |\n89: | `author_id` | `owner` | meta field |\n90: | `created_at` | `creation` | meta field |\n91: \n92: Not surfaced: `reactions` (Table → GP Reaction) — we model reactions as a\n93: flat lookup instead.\n94: \n95: ### `GPComment` ↔ `GP Comment`\n96: File: `gameplan/gameplan/doctype/gp_comment/gp_comment.json` · Autoname: autoincrement\n97: \n98: | TS field | Frappe field | Type |\n99: |---|---|---|\n100: | `id` | `name` | autoincrement |\n101: | `content` | `content` | Text Editor, reqd |\n102: | `reference_doctype` | `reference_doctype` | Link → DocType, value `\"GP Discussion\"` |\n103: | `reference_name` | `reference_name` | Dynamic Link |\n104: | `deleted_at` | `deleted_at` | Datetime (soft delete) |\n105: | `author_id` | `owner` | meta field |\n106: | `created_at` | `creation` | meta field |\n107: \n108: ### `GPReaction` ↔ `GP Reaction` *(child table, istable=1)*\n109: File: `gameplan/gameplan/doctype/gp_reaction/gp_reaction.json`\n110: \n111: In real Frappe this is a **child table** embedded inside both\n112: `GP Discussion.reactions` and `GP Comment.reactions`. The prototype flattens\n113: this into a top-level array keyed by `(reference_doctype, reference_name)`\n114: for ergonomics.\n115: \n116: | TS field | Frappe field | Type | Notes |\n117: |---|---|---|---|\n118: | `id` | `name` | autoincrement | |\n119: | `reference_doctype` | `parenttype` | implicit | `\"GP Discussion\"` or `\"GP Comment\"` |\n120: | `reference_name` | `parent` | implicit | the parent doc's `name` |\n121: | `user` | `user` | **Data** (not Link) | stored as user id string |\n122: | `emoji` | `emoji` | Data, reqd | |\n123: \n124: ### `GPUserProfile` ↔ `GP User Profile`\n125: File: `gameplan/gameplan/doctype/gp_user_profile/gp_user_profile.json` · Autoname: by script\n126: \n127: | TS field | Frappe field | Type |\n128: |---|---|---|\n129: | `user` | `user` | Link → User, reqd, unique |\n130: | `enabled` | `enabled` | Check (fetch_from user.enabled) |\n131: | `full_name` | `full_name` | Data (fetch_from user.full_name) |\n132: | `bio` | `bio` | Data, max 280 |\n133: | `readme` | `readme` | Text Editor |\n134: | `image` | `image` | Attach Image *(note: `image`, not `profile_image`)* |\n135: | `cover_image` | `cover_image` | Attach Image |\n136: | `image_background_color` | `image_background_color` | Color |\n137: \n138: Not surfaced: `cover_image_position`, `is_image_background_removed`,\n139: `original_image`.\n140: \n141: ## frappe/lms — stub only\n142: \n143: The prototype does **not** reimplement lessons, chapters, quizzes, batches,\n144: enrollments, or certificates. Those live in `frappe/lms`.\n145: \n146: ### `LMSCourse` ↔ `LMS Course`\n147: File: `lms/lms/doctype/lms_course/lms_course.json`\n148: \n149: | TS field | Frappe field | Type |\n150: |---|---|---|\n151: | `id` | `name` | |\n152: | `title` | `title` | Data |\n153: | `short_introduction` | `short_introduction` | Small Text |\n154: | `image` | `image` | Attach Image |\n155: | `paid_course` | `paid_course` | Check |\n156: | `featured` | `featured` | Check |\n157: | `enrollments` | `enrollments` | Int |\n158: | `lessons` | `lessons` | Int |\n159: | `category` | `category` | Link → LMS Category |\n160: \n161: ## fg_companion (new custom app)\n162: \n163: These DocTypes do not exist upstream. They will be defined in a new Frappe\n164: custom app called `fg_companion`. Names below are the canonical fieldnames\n165: to use when creating each DocType. Full Python recipe is in\n166: [`04_FRAPPE_TRANSLATION.md`](./04_FRAPPE_TRANSLATION.md).\n167: \n168: ### `FGEvent` → DocType `FG Event`\n169: \n170: | TS field | Frappe field | Type |\n171: |---|---|---|\n172: | `id` | `name` | autoname |\n173: | `title` | `title` | Data, reqd |\n174: | `description` | `description` | Long Text |\n175: | `space` | `space` | Link → GP Project (nullable) |\n176: | `event_type` | `event_type` | Select: Webinar / In-Person Meetup / Workshop / Drop-in Office Hours / Networking |\n177: | `starts_on` | `starts_on` | Datetime |\n178: | `ends_on` | `ends_on` | Datetime |\n179: | `location_type` | `location_type` | Select: Online (BigBlueButton) / Online (External Link) / In Person |\n180: | `bbb_meeting_id` | `bbb_meeting_id` | Data |\n181: | `external_link` | `external_link` | Data |\n182: | `physical_address` | `physical_address` | Small Text |\n183: | `rsvp_required` | `rsvp_required` | Check |\n184: | `capacity` | `capacity` | Int |\n185: | `hosted_by` | `hosted_by` | Link → User |\n186: \n187: ### `FGEventAttendee` → DocType `FG Event Attendee`\n188: \n189: | TS field | Frappe field | Type |\n190: |---|---|---|\n191: | `id` | `name` | |\n192: | `event` | `event` | Link → FG Event |\n193: | `user` | `user` | Link → User |\n194: | `rsvp_status` | `rsvp_status` | Select |\n195: \n196: ### `FGMentorMatch` → DocType `FG Mentor Match`\n197: \n198: | TS field | Frappe field | Type |\n199: |---|---|---|\n200: | `id` | `name` | |\n201: | `mentee` | `mentee` | Link → User |\n202: | `mentor` | `mentor` | Link → User |\n203: | `status` | `status` | Select |\n204: | `matched_on` | `matched_on` | Datetime |\n205: | `matched_via` | `matched_via` | Select |\n206: | `match_notes` | `match_notes` | Long Text |\n207: \n208: ### `FGAISettings` → Single DocType `FG AI Settings`\n209: \n210: | TS field | Frappe field | Type |\n211: |---|---|---|\n212: | `enable_sentiment` | `enable_sentiment` | Check (default 0) |\n213: | `sentiment_alert_threshold` | `sentiment_alert_threshold` | Float (default 0.75) |\n214: | `enable_vector_search` | `enable_vector_search` | Check (default 0) |\n215: \n216: ## Fields that do not map 1:1\n217: \n218: - `GPUserProfile.full_name` is `fetch_from: user.full_name` — it lives on\n219:   `User` in Frappe and is denormalised onto the profile.\n220: - `GPReaction` is a child table in Frappe (`istable=1`); the prototype\n221:   models it as a flat list to keep the React layer simple.\n222: - The mocked `SentimentLabel` and \"similar posts\" output are **not**\n223:   fields on any DocType — see [`04_FRAPPE_TRANSLATION.md`](./04_FRAPPE_TRANSLATION.md)\n224:   for the proper Frappe shape (Custom Fields on `GP Discussion`/`GP Comment` +\n225:   `doc_events` from the `fg_companion` app, never a fork of gameplan).\n\n(End of file - total 225 lines)\n</content>",
