      "type": "answer",
      "text": "**FRAME UP: Frappe Porting Plan**\n\nYour React prototype is **schema-faithful** to Frappe. Here's how to convert it to a real Frappe application:\n\n## Architecture\n```\nFrappe bench\n├── apps/frappe          (framework)\n├── apps/lms             (courses, lessons, quizzes)\n├── apps/gameplan        (teams, spaces, discussions, comments, reactions)\n└── apps/fg_companion    (NEW: events, mentor matching, AI hooks)\n```\n\n## 6-Step Porting Process\n\n**Step 0** 🔧 *Provisioning*  \n`bench init firstgens-bench --frappe-branch version-15`  \nInstall existing apps: `frappe/lms`, `frappe/gameplan`  \nCreate new app: `bench new-app fg_companion`\n\n**Step 1** ✅ *Keep gameplan as-is*  \nUse `frappe/gameplan` exactly as-is. TypeScript already matches their DocTypes.\n\n**Step 2** 📝 *Define new DocTypes*  \nCreate in `fg_companion`:\n- `FG Event`, `FG Event Attendee`, `FG Mentor Match`, `FG AI Settings`\n\n**Step 3** 🤖 *Wire AI features*  \nImplement sentiment analysis and vector search as `doc_events` in `fg_companion`.\n\n**Step 4** 🔌 *Swap data layer*  \nReplace `src/mock-data/store.ts` with Frappe HTTP client (same TypeScript types).\n\n**Step 5** 🔐 *Auth + permissions*  \nUse Frappe's session auth + role-based permissions matching gameplan's Space conventions.\n\n**Step 6** 🧹 *What to keep/discard*  \nKeep: all components, routes, types.ts  \nDiscard: mock data, AI stubs\n\nWhich step would you like to start with?",
      "timestamp": 1781965530465
    },
