      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Perfect! Now I have the complete Porting Guide. The user wants to \"frame it\" and make it \"fully frappe\", which means they want to convert this React prototype into a real Frappe application.\n\nLooking at the Porting Guide, it provides a clear 6-step process:\n\n1. Provisioning - setup the Frappe bench\n2. Keep gameplan DocTypes as-is (use existing apps)\n3. Define new DocTypes in fg_companion (new custom app)\n4. Wire AI features as doc_events\n5. Swap the React data layer from mock data to Frappe API\n6. Auth and permissions\n\nI should frame this up by showing them what they're about to do - convert their React prototype into a real Frappe application following the porting guide. This is a comprehensive process that involves:\n- Setting up a Frappe bench\n- Integrating existing Frappe apps (lms, gameplan)\n- Creating a new custom app (fg_companion)\n- Replacing mock data with real Frappe API calls\n- Implementing AI features via doc_events\n- Setting up proper permissions\n\nI should present this clearly and ask them which step they'd like to start with.",
