\n| |[v1.72.0](https://github.com/frappe/crm/releases/tag/v1.72.0) |May 22, 2026 Friday, 22 May 2026, 12:27 |Stable |\\n| |[v1.71.6](https://github.com/frappe/crm/releases/tag/v1.71.6) |May 19, 2026 Tuesday, 19 May 2026, 15:59 |Stable |\\n| |[v1.71.5](https://github.com/frappe/crm/releases/tag/v1.71.5) |May 18, 2026 Monday, 18 May 2026, 18:13 |Stable |\\n| |[v1.71.\\n4](https://github.com/frappe/crm/releases/tag/v1.71.4) |May 17, 2026 Sunday, 17 May 2026, 08:51 |Stable |\\n| |[v1.71.3](https://github.com/frappe/crm/releases/tag/v1.71.3) |May 15, 2026 Friday, 15 May 2026, 13:30 |Stable |\\n| |[v1.71.2](https://github.com/frappe/crm/releases/tag/v1.71.2) |May 11, 2026 Monday, 11 May 2026, 21:10 |Stable |\\n| |[v1.71.1](https://github.com/frappe/crm/releases/tag/v1.71.1) |May 11, 2026 Monday, 11 May 2026, 17:22 |Stable |\\n| |[v1.71.0](https://github.com/frappe/crm/releases/tag/v1.71.0) |May 8, 2026 Friday, 8 May 2026, 12:55 |Stable |\\n| |[v1.70.0](https://github.com/frappe/crm/releases/tag/v1.70.0) |Apr 28, 2026 Tuesday, 28 April 2026, 07:57 |Stable |\\n| |[v1.69.1](https://github.com/frappe/crm/releases/tag/v1.69.1) |Apr 21, 2026 Tuesday, 21 April 2026, 10:30 |Stable |\\n| |[v1.69.0](https://github.com/frappe/crm/releases/tag/v1.69.0) |Apr 20, 2026 Monday, 20 April 2026, 05:42 |Stable |\\n| |[v1.68.0](https://github.com/frappe/crm/releases/tag/v1.68.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/frappe/frappe\",\n      \"title\": \"GitHub - frappe/frappe: Low code web framework for real world applications, in Python and Javascript · GitHub\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"pre-commit-config.yaml |.pre-commit-config.yaml | | |\\n|.releaserc |.releaserc | | |\\n|.semgrepignore |.semgrepignore | | |\\n|CODEOWNERS |CODEOWNERS | | |\\n|CODE\\\\_OF\\\\_CONDUCT.md |CODE\\\\_OF\\\\_CONDUCT.md | | |\\n|LICENSE |LICENSE | | |\\n|README.md |README.md | | |\\n|SECURITY.md |SECURITY.md | | |\\n|attributions.md |attributions.md | | |\\n|babel\\\\_extractors.csv |babel\\\\_extractors.csv | | |\\n|codecov.yml |codecov.yml | | |\\n|commitlint.config.js |commitlint.config.js | | |\\n|crowdin.yml |crowdin.yml | | |\\n|cypress.config.js |cypress.config.js | | |\\n|generate\\\\_bootstrap\\\\_theme.js |generate\\\\_bootstrap\\\\_theme.js | | |\\n|hooks.md |hooks.md | | |\\n|node\\\\_utils.js |node\\\\_utils.js | | |\\n|package.json |package.json | | |\\n|pyproject.toml |pyproject.toml | | |\\n|sider.yml |sider.yml | | |\\n|socketio.js |socketio.js | | |\\n|yarn.lock |yarn.lock | | |\\n|View all files |\\n\\n## Repository files navigation\\n\\n* README\\n* Code of conduct\\n* Contributing\\n* MIT license\\n* Security\\n\\n# Frappe Framework\\n**Low Code Web Framework For Real World Applications, In Python And JavaScript**\\n\\n [](https://codecov.io/gh/frappe/frappe)\\n\\nHero Image\\n\\n[Website](https://frappe.io/framework) \\\\- [Documentation](https://docs.frappe.io/framework)\\n\\n## Frappe Framework\\n\\nFull-stack web application framework that uses Python and MariaDB on the server side and a tightly integrated client side library. Built for ERPNext.\\n\\n## Philosophy\\n\\n> The best code is the one that is not written\\n> \\n> \\n\\nStarted in 2005, Frappe Framework was inspired by the Semantic Web. The \\\"big idea\\\" behind semantic web was of a framework that not only described how information is shown (like headings, body etc), but also what it means, like name, address etc.\\n\\nBy creating a web framework that allowed for easy definition of metadata, it made building complex applications easy. Applications are usually designed around how users interact with a system, but not based on semantics of the underlying system.\\nApplications built on semantics end up being much more consistent and extensible.\\n\\nThe first application built on Framework was ERPNext, a beast with more than 700 object types. Framework is not for the light hearted - it is not the first thing you might want to learn if you are beginning to learn web programming, but if you are ready to do real work, then Framework is the right tool for the job.\\n\\n### Key Features\\n\\n* **Full-Stack Framework** : Frappe covers both front-end and back-end development, allowing developers to build complete applications using a single framework.\\n* **Built-in Admin Interface** : Provides a pre-built, customizable admin dashboard for managing application data, reducing development time and effort.\\n* **Role-Based Permissions** : Comprehensive user and role management system to control access and permissions within the application.\\n* **REST API** : Automatically generated RESTful API for all models, enabling easy integration with other systems and services.\\n\\n...\\n\\n[Pull Request Requirements](https://github.com/frappe/erpnext/wiki/Contribution-Guidelines)\\n4. [Translations](https://crowdin.com/project/frappe)\\n\\n  \\n  \\n[](https://frappe.io)\\n\\n## About\\n\\nLow code web framework for real world applications, in Python and Javascript\\n\\n[frappe.io/framework](https://frappe.io/framework \\\"https://frappe.io/framework\\\")\\n\\n### Topics\\n\\n### Resources\\n\\nReadme\\n\\n### License\\n\\nMIT license\\n\\n### Code of conduct\\n\\nCode of conduct\\n\\n### Contributing\\n\\nContributing\\n\\n### Security policy\\n\\nSecurity policy\\n\\nActivity\\n\\nCustom properties\\n\\n### Stars\\n\\n**10\\\\.3k** stars\\n\\n### Watchers\\n\\n**216** watching\\n\\n### Forks\\n\\n**5k** forks\\n\\nReport repository\\n\\n## Releases 1,563\\n\\nv15.112.0 Latest Jun 16, 2026\\n\\n\\\\+ 1,562 releases\\n\\n## Contributors\\n\\n* \\n* \\n*\\n\\n## Languages\\n\\n* Python 55\\\\.6%\\n* JavaScript 30\\\\.5%\\n* Vue 5\\\\.3%\\n* SCSS 3\\\\.5%\\n* HTML 2\\\\.7%\\n* TypeScript 1\\\\.8%\\n* Other 0\\\\.6%\\n\\n## Footer\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.erpnext.com/homepage\",\n      \"title\": \"ERPNext Documentation\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"* [Docs](https://docs.frappe.io/erpnext)\\n* [Github](https://www.github.com/frappe/erpnext)\\n* [Discuss](https://discuss.erpnext.com)\\n* [Videos](https://docs.frappe.io/erpnext/v13/user/videos/learn)\\n* \\n\\n[Start Free Trial](https://frappecloud.com/erpnext/signup)\\n\\n# ERPNext Documentation\\n\\nLearn how to use ERPNext and the Frappe Framework\\n\\n[View Docs →](https://docs.frappe.io/erpnext/introduction)\\n\\n## Core Modules\\n\\nPowerful, fully customisable base modules for your company\\n\\n### Accounting\\n\\nManage accounts, transactions and taxes easily with ERPNext\\n\\nLearn more →\\n\\n### Human Resource\\n\\nLeave and Attendance Tracking, Expense Claims, Salary and Payroll, Recruitment, Performance and more\\n\\nLearn more →\\n\\n### CRM\\n\\nTracking presales process from Lead capturing, tracking open Opportunities, to emails and calls\\n\\nLearn more →\\n\\n### Manufacturing\\nAn open source, modern cloud manufacturing ERP software that simplifies the production cycle, helps track material consumption, exhibits capacity planning, handles subcontracting, and more!\\n\\nLearn more →\\n\\n### Order Management\\n\\nIntelligently track order fulfillment, reduce incorrect inventory procurement, control stock levels, apply promotional schemes, and simplify your distribution business\\n\\nLearn more →\\n\\n### Asset Management\\n\\nEffectively manage assets, apply depreciation methods, asset capitalization and decapitalization all in one single place\\n\\nLearn more →\\n\\n## Developer Documentation\\n\\nLearn more about Frappe Framework, the rocket fuel to ERPNext\\n\\n### Frappe Framework\\n\\nERPNext is built using the Frappe Framework, a fully featured web framework in Python and Javascript\\n\\n[Learn more →](https://frappeframework.com)\\n\\n### Tutorial\\n\\nLearn the framework architecture by understanding how to build custom apps that can extend ERPNext\\n\\n[Learn more →](https://frappeframework.\\ncom/docs/user/en/tutorial)\\n\\n### Developer API\\n\\nLearn about how to build integrations and extensions for ERPNext by using the Developer API\\n\\n[Learn more →](https://frappeframework.com/docs/user/en/api)\\n\\n## Contribution & Feedback\\n\\nExplore, learn, contribute, and grow ERPNext\\n\\nERPNext is Open Source under the GNU General Public Licence v3 and has been listed as one of the best open source softwares in the world by many sites. Go on, send a pull request on the GitHub or join the discussion.\\n\\n[Contribute on Github →](https://github.com/frappe/erpnext)\\n\\nJoin our ever-growing list of 15,000+ contributors and make a difference to how ERP works\\n\\n[Join our Forums →](https://discuss.erpnext.com)\\n\\n‘Discuss’ is where our community gets together, shares new ideas, and helps each other out\\n\\nFooter Logo\\n\\n[ERPNext](https://www.erpnext.com) [Frappe Framework](https://frappeframework.com/docs) [Blog](https://erpnext.com/blog) [Contact](https://erpnext.com/contact-form)\\n\\n© Frappe.\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"warnings\": null,\n  \"usage\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"sku_search\",\n      \"count\": 1\n    }\n  ],\n  \"session_id\": \"ses_11a971471ffeOpwMX0xnBKt1oO\"\n}",
