      "text": "**FRAME UP: Frappe Porting Plan - LATEST v16**\n\nYour React prototype is **schema-faithful** to Frappe. Here's how to convert it to a real Frappe application using **v16** (released June 2026):\n\n## NEW v16 Architecture\n```\nFrappe bench v16\n├── apps/frappe          (v16 framework with ~2× performance)\n├── apps/lms             (courses, lessons, quizzes)\n├── apps/gameplan        (teams, spaces, discussions, comments)\n└── apps/fg_companion    (NEW custom app)\n```\n\n## NEW v16-Ready Porting Guide\n\n**Step 0** 🔧 *Provisioning with v16*\n```bash\n# Use latest Frappe v16\nbench init firstgens-bench --frappe-branch version-16\ncd firstgens-bench\n\n# Install apps\nbench new-site firstgens.local\nbench get-app https://github.com/frappe/lms\nbench get-app https://github.com/frappe/gameplan\nbench new-app fg_companion\n\nbench --site firstgens.local install-app lms gameplan fg_companion\n```\n\n**Step 1** ✅ *Keep gameplan as-is (v16 compatible)*\n- All existing gameplan DocTypes work unchanged with v16\n- Performance improvements apply automatically\n- No custom code needed\n\n**Step 2** 📝 *Define new DocTypes in v16*\nCreate in `fg_companion` using the same schema mapping from `01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md`\n\n**Step 3** 🚀 *Leverage v16 AI integrations*\n- **Role-based field masking** for AI sentiment labels\n- **Chrome-based PDF converter** for AI reports\n- **doc_events** for sentiment analysis and vector search\n\n**Step 4** ⚡ *Take advantage of v16 performance*\n- **~2× faster** API calls (no changes needed)\n- **Scrollability** in list views and child tables\n- **Sticky columns** for complex data\n\n**Step 5** 🔐 *Enhanced permissions with v16*\n- **Role-based field masking** for sensitive AI features\n- **Custom permission types** for FG Event, Attendee, Matches\n- **Built-in security** with v16's improved access control\n\n**Step 6** 🧹 *What stays/should be removed*\n**Stay:** All React components, routes, type shapes  \n**Remove:** Mock data, AI stubs, seed data\n\n## v16 Key Advantages\n- **~2× Performance** - All existing code runs faster\n- **Modern Workspace** - Better navigation and organization\n- **Scrollable Lists** - Handle large datasets better\n- **Enhanced Security** - Role-based field masking\n- **Better PDFs** - Chrome-based conversion\n\nWhich v16 step would you like to start with?",
