      "text": "I'm experiencing shell integration issues in your environment. Let me provide clear step-by-step instructions you can run manually:\n\n## **Option 1: Install Python 3.14 Manually**\n\n**Step 1: Install Python 3.14 from Python.org**\n```bash\n# Download Python 3.14 binary from python.org\nwget https://www.python.org/ftp/python/3.14.0/Python-3.14.0.tgz\ntar -xf Python-3.14.0.tgz\ncd Python-3.14.0\n./configure --enable-optimizations\nmake -j $(nproc)\nsudo make install\n```\n\n**Step 2: Install pip and venv**\n```bash\npython3.14 -m ensurepip --upgrade\npython3.14 -m pip install --upgrade pip\npython3.14 -m venv ~/frappe-bench/my-bench/env\n```\n\n**Step 3: Create bench**\n```bash\nbench init my-bench --frappe-branch version-16\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Option 2: Use Frappe v15** (Recommended - works with Python 3.12)\n\n```bash\n# If my-bench exists, remove it first\nrm -rf my-bench\n\n# Create bench with Frappe v15\nbench init my-bench --frappe-branch version-15\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Option 3: Docker** (Quickest solution)\n```bash\ndocker run -it --name frappe-bench -p 8000:8000 frappe/frappe-bench\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Current Status:**\n- ✅ pkg-config installed (from earlier)\n- ✅ Python 3.12 available (current system)\n- ❌ Python 3.14 not available (dead snakes PPA on noble/Ubuntu 24.04 doesn't provide Python 3.14)\n\n**My recommendation:** Go with **Option 2 (Frappe v15)** - it's the quickest path to get your prototype working. All your porting steps remain identical.\n\nWhich approach would you like to try?",
